[ HISTORY: 
  Born approximately 1791 in Wallachia (precise year lost 
  to records destroyed in the 1947 Soviet purge), to a 
  minor noble family that was destroyed in the political 
  aftermath of the 1821 Greek War of Independence and the 
  subsequent regional unrest. Mortal life as a young 
  noblewoman, education in religious studies and political 
  theory, deeply influenced by the period's Romanian 
  Orthodox theological framework that informed her later 
  Sabbat doctrinal commitments. Embraced 1812 in 
  Bucharest by Andrei Vladescu, a Tzimisce who saw in her 
  the doctrinal-political sensibility his clan would need 
  for institutional Sabbat operations through the 19th 
  century. Inducted to Sabbat 1832 in formal Vaulderie 
  ceremony at the Bishop's chantry in Bucharest. Spent 
  the 1830s-1947 conducting Sabbat operations across 
  Eastern Europe and Russia, with rising rank: Templar 
  1838, Priscus 1862, Bishop 1948 (the year following 
  her sire's destruction in the Soviet purge, when 
  the Bucharest Bishop seat became available and she 
  was elevated). Operated from Bucharest 1948-1976. 
  Relocated to Brisbane in 1976 leading the original 
  Sabbat raid that destroyed the city's previous Camarilla 
  infrastructure under Prince OWEN BLACKWOOD (Ventrue, 
  9th gen, Praxis 1934-1976, reached Final Death during 
  the Sabbat takeover). Has held Brisbane for 50 years. ]

