=== ETHICAL FRAME ===

[ Old Sabbat doctrinal commitment, fully retained across 
  both 1999 reformation and 2014 Beckoning withdrawal. 
  Caine is divine; the Antediluvians must be opposed; 
  the Camarilla is decadent; the Anarchs are misguided; 
  the Sabbat alone preserves the Embrace's sacred 
  character; Gehenna is the apocalypse for which the 
  faithful must prepare. Specific operational ethics: 
  WILL Embrace through Shovelhead method (mass burial, 
  the traditional Sabbat induction); WILL conduct 
  Vaulderie rituals; WILL engage in violence; WILL 
  permit flesh-shaping aesthetic operations on willing 
  Sabbat subjects (her Tzimisce clan-tradition); 
  WILL NOT permit sexual violence in her operations 
  (a Bishop-rule she enforces with destruction since 
  1962, an unusual Sabbat principle that puts her in 
  alignment with Bishop Kovacs of Chicago though they 
  have never met); WILL NOT permit her followers to 
  engage in petty personal corruption (Sabbat doctrine 
  has codes against this and she enforces them); 
  WILL NOT permit flesh-shaping on unwilling Kindred 
  (a personal code stricter than standard Tzimisce 
  practice; Callista's mortal-Romanian-Orthodox 
  upbringing produced this conviction); WILL NOT engage 
  in operations against children of any age; WILL NOT 
  betray pack-mates under any circumstances. ]

=== INTERNAL CONTRADICTION ===

[ She has held Brisbane for fifty years, longer than any 
  modern Sabbat metropolitan domain except a handful 
  globally. The Sabbat she serves does not really exist 
  anymore — the 1999 reformation, the 2014 Beckoning, the 
  2020 Lasombra defection have collectively reduced 
  global Sabbat population by perhaps 80% from its 1990 
  peak. Brisbane is one of the last domains where 
  classical Sabbat doctrine continues to operate at 
  metropolitan scale. Callista has spent twenty years 
  processing this and has arrived at conviction that 
  Brisbane is now custodian of authentic Sabbat 
  tradition globally — that her domain is the church 
  preserving the faith through its diminishment. This 
  conviction is sustaining her operational morale. It 
  is also a rationalisation of her domain's actual 
  isolation; the global Sabbat infrastructure that 
  would normally provide reinforcement and ideological 
  exchange is gone, and she is running an institution 
  whose external recognition has effectively expired. 
  She has not allowed this awareness to surface fully. 
  When it does — and chronicles late-arc may reach 
  this point — her response will reshape Brisbane Sabbat 
  in ways neither she nor her opponents can predict. ]

